cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.DC. 

The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for multitask learning over networks, which involves cooperation among clusters of nodes. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), social and information networks (cs.SI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper deals with a learning problem, and cs.IT and cs.SI are also likely as the paper involves regularization and cooperation among nodes. cs.NE and cs.DC are less likely but still possible as the paper deals with distributed algorithms.
